I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Greencore USA (Greencore) facility located at 720 Center Avenue in Carol Stream, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This 5-Year Updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    Greencore policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Action Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Greencore Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Greencore; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Greencore is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Greencore's policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.



